Also, I don&#39;t remember if I&#39;ve mentioned this yet, but I have started a 
CVS repository of published reaction mechanisms converted to Cantera 
cti format.  The LLNL ethanol mechanism is one of the ones already in 
the repository.  You can get it by going to the Cantera Sourceforge 
site, selecting &quot;CVS&quot;, then selecting the link in the right-hand column 
labeled &quot;Browse the CVS Repository&quot;. Then click on &quot;reactionmechs&quot;, 
then &quot;llnl&quot;, and then select the ethanol mechanism file.  
Alternatively, you can check out the entire &quot;reactionmechs&quot; module 
using anonymous CVS.


