&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ck2cti converts it to cti format with no problem, but there are
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; three-body
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; falloff reactions that have different low-pressure coefficients
&gt;&gt; for
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; different third bodies and Cantera has problems with that.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The reactions are:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; #  Reaction 4
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; falloff_reaction( &quot;h + o2 (+ M) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ M)&quot;,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;          kf = [4.52000E+013, 0, 0],
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;          kf0   = [1.05000E+019, -1.257, 0],
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;          efficiencies = &quot; ch4:10  co:1.9  co2:3.8  h2:0  h2o:0
&gt;&gt; n2:0 &quot;)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; #  Reaction 5
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; falloff_reaction( &quot;h + o2 (+ n2) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ n2)&quot;,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;          kf = [4.52000E+013, 0, 0],
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;          kf0   = [2.03000E+020, -1.59, 0])
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (and two others with n2 and h2o as third bodies)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The error I get with Cantera is:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Procedure: installReaction
